text: Interested in creating your own custom mechanical keyboard without breaking the bank?
Discover how to assemble a keyboard using the GMK87 TKL kit,
Occo Cream Yellow switches, and XDA PBT keycaps.
This guide includes key mods like lubing switches and stabilizers,
the tape mod for enhanced acoustics, and adding a coiled cable.
Ideal for beginners seeking a satisfying typing experience on a budget.
